OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGrenfell Tower: Man admits 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fposting grossly offensive  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fmodel video                
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A man has admitted sharing a grossly   
OL,6, offensive video of a cardboard model of
OL,7, Grenfell Tower being burned on a       
OL,8, bonfire.                               
OL,10,FPaul Bussetti, of Sundial Avenue in    
OL,11,FCroydon, south London, pleaded guilty  
OL,12,Fat Westminster Magistrates' Court.     
OL,14,FThe clip was recorded at a party in    
OL,15,Fsouth London a year after the Grenfell 
OL,16,FTower fire in 2017, which killed 72    
OL,17,Fpeople, and was shared on WhatsApp.    
OL,19,FThe 49-year-old was given a 10-week    
OL,20,Fsuspended jail sentence.               
